📧 Task 4: Professional Communication & Digital Etiquette
Role: Student Digital Ambassador

Objective: Mastering the art of professional correspondence and responsible digital citizenship.

📋 Overview
As a Student Digital Ambassador, clear and ethical communication is the cornerstone of leadership. This task focuses on the "soft skills" of digital literacy—specifically, the ability to navigate high-stakes professional environments through email and the ability to maintain a responsible social media presence. By mastering these protocols, I aim to model the standard for peer-to-peer and student-to-professional interactions within our academic batch.

🔍 Part A: Professional Email Correspondence
Effective communication requires a balance of clarity, courtesy, and structure. I have developed two primary templates that demonstrate high-level email etiquette:

Academic Request (Extension): An email addressed to a professor requesting an assignment extension. This draft emphasizes transparency, accountability, and the use of a formal subject line to ensure academic professionalism.

Professional Outreach (Internship): A cold-outreach email to an Internship Coordinator. This highlights my interest in summer opportunities while maintaining a concise, value-driven body and a professional sign-off.

Both documents adhere to the "Five Pillars of Email Etiquette": Clear Subject, Professional Salutation, Purposeful Body, Call to Action, and Formal Signature.

🔍 Part B: Social Media "Do's and Don'ts"
To guide my peers toward responsible digital citizenship, I have authored a comprehensive Social Media Checklist. This resource provides 10 actionable guidelines (5 Do’s and 5 Don’ts) specifically tailored for college students. It covers critical areas such as:

Privacy Settings & Security: Protecting personal data.

Content Curation: Understanding that a digital footprint is permanent.

Network Integrity: Engaging in constructive, rather than destructive, online discourse.

